<subSubSection id="C963DAC0013F43DCB080C04389CEC31F" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" type="derivation of specific epithet">
<paragraph id="F11502CF9F918939A1E9AF9EEF701D05" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Derivation of specific epithet.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="93D73DE5C6AF763C6192A23F6D850642" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
The epithet 
<normalizedToken id="37A0E74EC02213D933DC42E8672A388F" originalValue="“batesi”">
&quot; 
<emphasis id="1CC4374DD0EF3C1F041485B0AF6AE917" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">batesi</emphasis>
&quot;
</normalizedToken>
is an eponym, based on the family name of Henry Walter Bates, whose eleven years of collecting beetles in South America capturing adults of many new species, and genera such as this, would qualify him for the Hall of Fame of beetle collectors and describers, if there was such a Hall.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DA419E347BF3DCDCE0E5436C76CE3A1" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" type="proposed english vernacular name">
